HEADWORD: Catmint
<hw>Cat"mint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A well-know plant of the
genus <gen>Nepeta</gen> (<spn>Nepeta Cataria</spn>), somewhat like mint,
having a string scent, and sometimes used in medicine. It is so called
because cats have a peculiar fondness for it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cato-cathartic</ent>⟦br⟧
